"v.细查；拉选票 【英】 v. 细查; 拉选票(go around an area asking people for political support) 【考】 exponent : advocate / pollster : canvass(倡导者提倡/民意测 验家调查民意) 【例】 go out canvassing for votes v. 民意调查; 拉选票; 仔细检查 = scrutinize 【例】canvass a district for votes 为争取选票在选举区游说 【记】源自canvas(n 帆布), 原来的民意调查结果是写在帆布上的. 【类】exponent: advocate = pollster: canvass倡导者提倡 = 民意测验家调查民意 【记】canvase 油布，油布式游说，近于常见的地毯式(调查，搜寻) canvass (v.)  c.1500, from alternative spelling of canvas (n.) and probably meaning, originally, ""to toss or sift in a canvas sheet,"" hence ""to shake out, examine carefully"" (1520s); ""to solicit votes"" (1550s). The spelling with a double -s- dates from 16c. Compare Old French canabasser ""to examine carefully,"" literally ""to sift through canvas."" Related: Canvassed; canvassing. As a noun related to this, attested from c.1600."
